{"/service/ndnp/nvln/batch_nvln_hiko_ver01/data/sn86076249/00332891364/1908062401/0654.xml":{"full_text":"MINING, MARKETS AND METALS\nINCLINED TO LOWER.\nTrend of I'rln-s Downward on Small\nAmount of ItusinoKs\u20144>|\u00bberntor*\nHave Doubts.\nNEW YORK. June\"2?, The weak\nness of stocks today gave an impres\nsion of l\u00bbss i-assiveness than the oc\ncasional drop with intervals of re\ncovery last week There was only\nsmall expansion in the volume of the\ndealings to account for this appear\nunce The active desire shown to\nget out of holdings of one or two\nftcfks was largely accountable for\nhie changed tone of tin* dealings\nRock Island securities were the con\nspicuous example. In continuance of\na sudden decline which commenced\nIn the closing dealings on Saturday\nand which had a considerable influ\nence in unsettling the tone. The ru\nmors which circulated today in con\nnection with the break in Rock Isl\nand seemed to Ik- more in tin* nature\nof surmise prompted by the move\nment of the stocks than any informed\nopinions The movement gave rise\nto some fears of financial embarrass\nment facing the company or some\none of its related companies in the\ncomplicated series of subsidiaries\nwhich distinguishes these enterprises.\nMore than once during the last few\nmonths It has been reported that a\ncomprehensive reorganization plan\nwas in contemplation Today's ru\nmors hinted at a coming bond issue,\nand even at a receivership, hut these\nru*noi were discredited in \u00bbfltcial\n\u2022juarters Another supposition was\nof heavy losses from flood damage to\nthe company\u2019s property, but this was\ndenied by officials of the company\nThe weakness of the Rock Island se\ncurities was of sympathetic effect on\nthe whole stork market.\nThere was nothing in the general\nnews to prompt selling of stocks. The\naccumulation of hanking reserves is\nreaching a point that seems to neces\nsitate active measures to find em\nploymenf for these great sums. Paris\ntook gold from Ixindon today and the\nunsatisfied appetite of that center\nand of Berlin for the precious* metal\nconstitutes the only ripple is the\nmoney market Reports of the plac\ning of part of the new bond issue of\nthe National railroad of Mexico with\nParis bankers were believed to ex\nplain the decline in our foregn ex\nchange* market. Traffic officials of\nthe great railroad system spoke In a\ntone- of some encouragement of the\nbusiness outlook, although having\nactual outlook, although having\nsmall actual Increase in tonnage\nYesterday was another practically\nfeatureless day in the* market. It\nlooks more and more like a season\nof inaction and summer quiet at\nhand. The El.vs are holding their\nown. with little show for material\nchange at any immediate date. The\nmetal quotations show small varia\ntions \u00abin the cpiotation lists as posted\nbut it is known that copper, silver\nand lead an* all selling higher than\nmarket prices. Copper is particular\nly strong. Yeste rday\u2019s closing quota\ntions were:\nBid Asked.\nNevada Con 11.62% 11.87\nClimb Ely 7.50 7.62\nCiroux Con 3 37% 3.50\nEly Con 18 .22\nNew house 6.12% 6.25\nCopper 12\nSilver .'*4\nLend 4.50\nMoney, 1 *4 per cent\nIII N I i Hilt x m i.SE LETTER.\nThe market was very dull today.\nThe public is out of the market and\nbetter prices cannot Is* expected un\ntil confidence is restored. Ely stoc ks\nare not very active but are holding\nstrong The metal market is much\nI\u00bbetter and prices are working to\nhigher levels every day\nELY CITY DIRECTORY OF RELIABLE\nBUSINESS HOUSES\nThr Various liinra of Ituftim-s* Ri-prew-ntcd in Hj City. a* fJlyrn\nKotow an- Onndort\u00abl by Thorou(thl y Onni|H-ti-nt and Itilinbb- IlnKlni-xa\nMrn of tin- Community.\nUuualt Thnr i'tnh tur AdibmiM anil Tlrphonr Numlrn When\ntankini; for Ibr Itight IMarm for ItiRlit ltuntni\u2018K* Ibnlinir*.\nA I\nABHKY BAB.\n411 Wklnklra Bought\nIMreet from Hoad\nPb\u00bb*r tin.\nANTIiKH IIAlt.\nt ______\nJ. II. Fulmer, Mgr.\nHea